In Fig. 29 we show a color map of such a KL divergence Eq. (3.17) comparing the participation spectra

of half ladders for various rung couplings J2/J1 against the effective short-range Heisenberg chain model Eq. (3.12) in the parameter space spanned by the effective inverse temperature βeﬀ and the entanglement length ξE. We clearly see a minimum of the KL divergence with a very small magnitude < 10−4, in good agreement with the perturbative result Eqs. (3.13)(3.14). The KL divergence provides a very precise

qualitative tool to test the validity of a given entanglement Hamiltonian.

