Sj

.

(3.19)

In Fig. 32 we provide a direct comparison between the short-range model Eq. (3.12) and the one with power-law interactions Eq. (3.19) for g = 0.5, i.e. very close to the quantum critical coupling of the d = 2 dimerized Hamiltonian Eq. (3.18). The latter model clearly displas a much better agreement, with an effective inverse temperature βeﬀ J1 1, and a power α 2.
b. Ne´el ordered regime— Keeping the same one-dimensional setup for subsystem A, one can cross the critical point and explore the Ne´el ordered side for g > gc, as done in Refs. [194, 195]. In this regime, while the power-law model Eq. (3.19) gives reasonable KL (Fig. 33 top) for parameters (α − βeﬀ ) where

