The distribution of Tr ρ2A , shown in the main panel of Fig. 35 for the random singlet state of random XX chains (exact diagonalization results) for increasing system lengths L = 16, . . . , 512, displays broad-

ening at small values with increasing size, suggesting non-self-averaging entanglement10. In the inset of

Fig. 35, the log scalings are plotted for q = 1, 2, showing a very good agreement with the analytical pre-

diction Eq (4.1) and (4.2).

