inter−ladd.

(5.12)

This model displays two gapped rung-singlet phases if the inter-ladder coupling λ1c > λ > λ2c with λ1c = 0.31407(5) [381] and λ2c = 1.9096(2) [384], and a gapless Ne´el ordered phase in between, as shown in Fig. 53 (a). T = 0 ﬂuctuations of the total magnetization in a sub-system A of size L/2 × L, embedded in

a periodic square lattice L × L are shown in Fig. 53 (b-c), with square lattices size up to L × L = 104, for

the isotropic square lattice λ = 1 (Ne´el) and for weakly coupled ladders with λ = 0.1 (gapped rung singlet

I). In contrast with the entanglement (or Re´nyi) entropy which displays a strict area law both phases, the

second cumulant follows different scalings [94]:

